Create a UDP file on both Master and Slave
modify Slave's terminal: sudo python path/to/foo.py
modify Slave's: nano ~/.config/lxsession/LXDE-pi/autostart
		Add at the bottom: @lxterminal
		
This causes that at boot up the terminal is opned
Since inside the terminal we are calling our script
 it gets executed at boot up
However, everytime a new terminal window is open
that script is called again. and again..
One case will be SSH